      "message": "[CL Review Agent] If `_LsRemote` returns whitespace characters (such as `\\n`), `output` will evaluate as truthy, but `output.splitlines()` will return an empty list `[]`. This would cause `output.splitlines()[0]` on the next line to raise an `IndexError`.\n\nConsider making this check more robust, for example:\n```python\n            if output and output.splitlines():\n```",
